just one of the guys transgender men and the persistence of gender inequality events at stanford just one of the guys transgender men and the persistence of gender inequality facebook twitter email print add to calendar in the second installment of the clayman institute's spring 2011 event series author kristen schilt assistant professor of sociology at the university of chicago will discuss her book just one of the guys which analyzes workplace inequalities facing the highly understudied transgender population just one of the guys addresses the unequal treatment that men and women continue to receive at work by exploring the common explanations for this disparity range from biological differences between the sexes to the conscious and unconscious biases that guide hiring and promotion decisions the book sheds a new light on this phenomenon by analyzing the unique experiences of transgender men people designated female at birth whose gender identity is male on the job this event is co sponsored by the sociology department and feminist studies it is free and open to all books will be available for sale at the event when thursday may 12 2011 4 15 pm approximate duration of 1.5 hour s where levinthal hall stanford humanities center 424 santa teresa street map audience faculty staff alumni friends general public students members tags humanities other sponsor program in feminist studies clayman institute for gender research contact 725 0373 ann enthoven stanford edu admission free and open to all permalink http events stanford edu events 272 27271 more info last modified may 11 2011
